     Done! Built 97 pages in docs/

● Refresh **http://localhost:8000/week01.html** — both interactive iframes now
  self-size to their actual content.

**How it works:** each interactive HTML measures
  `document.documentElement.scrollHeight` after Plotly finishes laying out
  and posts it to the parent via
  `postMessage({type:'lesson-interactive-resize', height: N})`. The parent
  (`SITE_JS`) listens for that message, finds the matching iframe by
  `e.source === iframe.contentWindow`, and snaps `iframe.style.height` to
  the reported pixel value.

Result:
- **Three-portfolios chart** — stays at ~770px (its actual content height).
- **Inflation chart** — collapses from the 770px default down to its real
  ~680px, no more white bar.
- **Any future interactive** — auto-fits without needing per-asset CSS or
  magic numbers in `build.py`.

The `ResizeObserver` on `<body>` also re-fires on window-resize, on theme
  switch (chart re-renders), and whenever Plotly redraws — so the iframe
  stays right-sized as the user interacts with sliders or rotates a phone.

