  properly inside list items and prose.

**To use math in any future lesson:**

```markdown
Display math (centered block):
\[ E = mc^2 \]

Inline math: \(E = mc^2\) sits in the line.

Multi-line aligned:
\[ \begin{aligned}
y &= mx + b \\
  &= 2x + 5
\end{aligned} \]
```

Anything KaTeX supports — fractions, integrals, summations, matrices, Greek
  letters, the `aligned` / `cases` / `matrix` environments — will render.
  Full reference: <https://katex.org/docs/supported.html>.

